Police on Thursday arrested the father of one of the suspects in the case of missing Alabama teenager Natalee Holloway, saying he may have knowledge of her mysterious disappearance.
Joran van der Sloot and his Surinamese friends, brothers Deepak Kalpoe, 21, and Satish Kalpoe, 18, were arrested June 9.
No one has been charged.
Van der Sloot's mother, Anita, has said her son told her he was alone with Holloway on the beach but he did not harm her.
